					<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Refutation">Refutation</span></h1>
<p>Refutation is showing an argument in unsuccessful (invalid, fallacy, etc.). There are several ways to refute an argument:</p>
<ul>
<li>Counter-example: an example that runs against a generalization</li>
<li>Reductio ad Absurdum (reduction to absurdity): refute by showing that if the argument was true it would lead to something absurd</li>
<li>Straw man (fallacy): trying to misrepresent the argument</li>
<li>False dichotomy (fallacy): claims that there are only two options (the desired conclusion and something clearly unacceptable)</li>
<li>Parallel reasoning: refute the argument by producing a parallel argument of the same form which is obviously wrong (invalid)</li>
</ul>

